June 2 (Reuters) - McDonald's Corp (MCD.N) will have an option to buy its restaurants in Russia back within 15 years, Russia's anti-monopoly service said in a statement on Thursday. The service approved a deal in which the fast-food company sold the restaurants to one of its local licensees - Alexander Govor, who will rebrand them, ending more than three decades of the "Golden Arches" in the country.  read more  Our Standards: The Thomson Reuters Trust Principles.